                        <persName xml:lang="fa">عاملى، بهاء الدين محمد بن حسين</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_2067">Nān va ḥalvā</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_2067">نان وحلوا</title>
                     <note>Frony flyleaf, recto: Note of price as 1/-. Loose withing the manuscrit: a) Slip pencilled with: Storey Collection (This appears to be the only evidence that the MS came from Storey) b) Slip again giving the price as 1/- only. c) Card with a description of Diwan of Lami'i dated 1308 and designated No 10 and as from C.A. Storey. d) Slip with number given by A.H.M. Board and marbled paper cover. Loose. The number is assigned by A.H.M., April 2010. A mathnawi poem composed during the Hajj, with a brief prose introduction in Arabic. Headings in red.</note>
                     <incipit>Hamd allah (sic) 'ala ifdalihi</incipit>
